<subSubSection pageId="23" pageNumber="24" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="23" pageNumber="24">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="23" pageNumber="24">
This appears to be the first record in the scientific literature of this species since its description. It was originally described from Sri Lanka, and most photographic records are from the type locality, with a few from Thailand and Burma to the east (
<bibRefCitation author="NudiPixel website," journalOrPublisher="Journal Marine Biological Association, India" pageId="66" pageNumber="67" url="http://www.nudipixel.net/" year="1968">NudiPixel</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Sea Slug Forum website," journalOrPublisher="Zoological Journal Linnean Society" pageId="67" pageNumber="68" url="http://www.seaslugforum.net/" year="1987">Sea Slug Forum</bibRefCitation>
). The species described as 
<taxonomicName class="Gastropoda" family="Discodorididae" genus="Halgerda" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Halgerda punctata" order="Nudibranchia" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="punctata">Halgerda punctata</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Rudman, WB" journalOrPublisher="Zoological Journal Linnean Society" pageId="67" pageNumber="68" pagination="59 - 88" title="The dorid opisthobranch genera Halgerda Bergh and Sclerodoris Eliot from the Indo-West Pacific." url="10.1111/j.1096-3642.1978.tb00523.x" volume="62" year="1978">Rudman (1978)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Gosliner, TM" journalOrPublisher="A guide to Opisthobranch molluscs of Southern Africa. EJ Brill, Leiden, Netherlands" pageId="65" pageNumber="66" title="Nudibranchs of Southern Africa." year="1987">Gosliner (1987)</bibRefCitation>
were re-identified as 
<taxonomicName class="Gastropoda" family="Discodorididae" genus="Halgerda" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Halgerda formosa" order="Nudibranchia" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="formosa">Halgerda formosa</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Fahey, SJ" journalOrPublisher="Proceedings of the California Academy Sciences" pageId="65" pageNumber="66" pagination="365 - 383" title="Description of three new species of Halgerda from the western Indian Ocean with a redescription of Halgerda formosa, Bergh 1880." url="10.1046/j.1463-6409.2001.00054.x" volume="51" year="1999">Fahey and Gosliner (1999)</bibRefCitation>
, so it appears no one has found or redescribed 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Farran’s">Farran's</normalizedToken>
species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
